comments.body:
@yiminc migration tool  I mean `temporal-*-tool`, and the depended migration files. Currently have to enter the docker image to do the migration job, setup-schema & update, or run from source, the migration files is not bundled in `temporal-*-tool`.

I think tctl can integrate `temporal-*-tool`'s function, reduce the setup work.

For later, temporal may introduce sqlite, may even add tools to migration data from sqlite to other db. tctl contain all these tool's functions, one tool for all job.
